# Literature Review: Digital Transformation of the Maritime Industry: A Cybersecurity Systemic Approach

## Introduction

The maritime industry is undergoing a significant transformation as information system solutions are
increasingly being applied, leading to the digital transformation of the industry. This digital transformation
has the potential to revolutionize all aspects of maritime operations. However, with the adoption of
new technologies and reliance on information technologies, the maritime industry faces cybersecurity
challenges. This literature review aims to explore the existing research findings related to the digital
transformation of the maritime industry and its implications for cybersecurity. By synthesizing the
provided research insights, this review will highlight the key findings, identify knowledge gaps, and
suggest potential future research directions.

## Digital Transformation in the Maritime Industry

The concept of digital transformation encompasses the integration of digital technologies into various
sectors and industries, including the maritime industry. Digital transformation involves the adoption
and utilization of information technologies to enhance efficiency, productivity, and competitiveness.
According to Matt et al. (2015), digital transformation strategies help organizations leverage technological
advancements to gain a competitive edge and improve their overall performance in the industry [^1].
The maritime industry's digital transformation involves the implementation of information system solutions that can streamline operations, enable real-time data exchange, and facilitate automation. This
transformation has the potential to revolutionize the industry by enhancing operational efficiency, reducing costs, and improving decision-making processes [^1]. Moreover, digital transformation enables the
integration of various technologies, such as the Internet of Things (IoT), cloud computing, and artificial
intelligence, into maritime operations, leading to the development of smart ports and vessels [^3].

## Cybersecurity Challenges in the Maritime Industry

As the maritime industry embraces digital transformation, it also faces cybersecurity challenges. The
increasing reliance on information technologies and interconnected systems exposes the industry to
cyber threats and attacks. Cyberattacks in the maritime industry can have severe consequences, including
disruption of operations, compromise of sensitive data, and potential threats to maritime safety and
security [^5].
